    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Hungarian Chamber to Miklós Oláh (Bratislava, 8 January
                    1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>The postmaster handed over a stack of letters that also included Oláh’s
                            letter to them, indicating that royal letters should be written to
                            András (Bonaventura) Báthori and Georg Werner, which they will gladly
                            do. They inform Oláh that three knights of the Chamber were sent to
                            Košice, Prešov, and other places further away, while the fourth has
                            returned empty-handed; the King sent all four of them in the matter of
                            the revenues. It is impossible for them to take care of both the
                            Chamber’s and the King’s affairs, so they ask him to choose a more
                            appropriate route when sending letters, and because the Palatine has
                            several knights who should be looking after the royal affairs, they
                            should entrust such letters to them instead of the Chamber, which only
                            has ten knights, who cannot tackle so many cases.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ad dominum cancellarium.</p>
                <p>Reverendissime Domine, Domine et Patrone Observandissime, servitiorum nostrae
                    commendationem!</p>
                <p>Reddidit <persName>magister postarum</persName><note type="critic">Matthias Taxis
                        was Postmaster general <hi rend="italic">(supremus postarum magister)</hi>
                        between 1548 and 1558, see <hi rend="smallcap">Ember</hi> 1946,
                        375–376.</note> regiae maiestatis hodie fasciculum litterarum, <del
                        corresp="author">quibus</del><add corresp="author" type="corr">cui</add> et
                    Reverendissimae Dominationis Vestrae litterae <add corresp="author"
                        type="insert">ad nos</add> erant insertae significantes oportere, ut
                    litterae regiae ad dominum <persName>Bathory</persName><note type="critic"
                        >András (Bonaventura) Báthori.</note> et <persName><add corresp="author"
                            type="insert">Georgium</add> Vernerum</persName>,<note type="critic"
                        >Georg Werner.</note> citissime<note type="critic">Uncertain reading.</note>
                    dirigentur. Nos quidem perlibenter id facimus, quod a sua maiestate iubemur.
                    Certa tamen sit Reverendissima Dominatio Vestra abesse ad
                        <placeName>Cassoviam</placeName>,<note type="critic">Košice.</note> ad
                        <placeName>Epperies</placeName><note type="critic">Prešov.</note> et remota
                    alia loca missos tres equites Camerae, quartus post longissima itinera hodie est
                    reversus ita, ut per quem mittamur litterae, nullus sit ad manum. Hos autem
                    quattuor equites ad negotia tamen proventuum maiestas regia hinc Camerae
                    attribuit, ad quem etiam vix sufficiunt, ut necesse <del corresp="author"
                        >sit</del> videantur ea, quae negotium regiae maiestatis concernent vel
                    reverendissimo domino <persName>locumtenenti</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Ferenc Újlaki.</note> imponi et iniugi, vel alium modum excogitari.
                    Impossibile est enim <del corresp="author">ut</del>, ut et Camerae et regiae
                    maiestatis negotia <add corresp="author" type="insert">omnia</add> nos curemus
                    opera quattuor equitum, non tutum est litteras maioris momenti occurrentibus et
                    incertis hominibus committi. </p>
                <p>Quare Reverendissimam Dominationem Vestram rogamus plurimum, velit servare in
                    directione litterarum <del corresp="author">talem</del> eum modum, qui
                    possibilis sit et cum plures habeant equites domini locumtenentis, cui negotia
                    regiae maiestatis succumbunt, iustius illi commendabuntur tales litterae, quam
                    Camerae, quae tot difficultatibus perpetuo urgetur, ut ad sola Camerae negotia
                    vix decem equites sufficerent. <del corresp="author">Non est locus
                        extraordinariis expensis cursorem in ratione ibi nollemus.</del> Quod
                    imprimis Reverendissimae Dominationi Vestrae voluimus significare, quam optamus
                    valere feliciter.</p>
                <p><placeName>Posonii</placeName> die 8. Ianuarii anno 1552.</p>
                <p>Reverendissimae Dominationis Vestrae deditissimi servitores</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Camerae Hungaricae regiae maiestatis consiliarii.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
